Advance Excel Assignment 4 


 
1. To use the ribbon commands, what menu and grouping of commands will you find the Insert and Delete command? 
Ans :  After using ribbon and go to the home tab and find cell (group of menu) and find Insert and delete command .


2. If you set a row height or column width to 0 (zero), what happens to the row and column? 
Ans ; If I set the column and row width to zero , the bunch of the cell total hide, but it exist okay .


3. Is there a need to change the height and width in a cell? Why? 
Ans ; Yes , while we find out the particular cell have more contain , look so odd then we need to change the height and width.


 
4. What is the keyboard shortcut to unhide rows? 
Ans ; Ctrl +shift +9 is the short cut to unhide rows.


 
5. How to hide rows containing blank cells? 
Ans; Select the range and go the data tab and select filter and then filter the blanks . 


 
6. What are the steps to hide the duplicate values using conditional formatting in excel? 
Ans; First select the range and go the conditional formatting and and go to all rules and then  select dupcate and unique and then this will paint the duplicate and go to formula tab and delete / hide duplicate , via this we can hide the duplicate values using conditional formatting.


 

